
[1]pet

   PET, n. [This word may be contracted from petulant, or belong to the
   root of that word. Peevish, which is evidently a contracted word, may
   be from the same root.]

   A slight fit of peevishness or fretful discontent.

   Life given for noble purposes must not be thrown away in a pet, nor
   whined away in love.

                      PET, n. [formerly peat. L. peto.]

   1. A cade lamb; a lamb brought up by hand.

   2. A fondling; any little animal fondled and indulged.

             PET, v.t. To treat as a pet; to fondle; to indulge.
